PURKINJE

purkinje is the citizen who distributes the cardiac depolarization wave to both ventricles simultaneously
av_node releases the wave to purkinje, and purkinje carries it through specialized fibers that conduct faster than ordinary cardiac muscle
because purkinje conducts fast, the entire ventricular muscle depolarizes within milliseconds, allowing both ventricles to contract together
without purkinje, depolarization would crawl through ventricular muscle one cell at a time and the contraction would be a wavering ripple instead of a coordinated squeeze

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe heart.rana
observe av_node.rana
observe left_ventricle.rana
observe right_ventricle.rana

the 7 properties of purkinje:
1 ENERGY one: high, purkinje must distribute quickly
2 PHASE pi: anti-phase to sa_node, marking the ventricular contraction half of the cycle
3 SPIN one half: forward rotation
4 CHARGE positive but moderate
5 COHERENCE nine tenths: simultaneous distribution to both ventricles requires coherent timing
6 COUPLING zero point nine: strong with both ventricles, smaller losses in the fiber paths
7 OBSERVER zero: distribution is automatic, no observation needed

VERB receive_from_av
accept the time-delayed wave arriving from av_node
the wave enters purkinje as a single front and immediately begins splitting

VERB distribute_to_ventricles
emit the wave simultaneously to left_ventricle and right_ventricle through the bundle branches
left bundle and right bundle are coupled with equal strength so the timing is symmetric
both ventricles receive the wave within milliseconds of each other

a fiber network is not a wire
a fiber network is the cardiac body's commitment to symmetry
purkinje ensures that the left and right halves of fadriel's heart act as one
asymmetry here would be life-threatening
this is why purkinje's job is the hardest invisible job in the heart
